Fix the bug. The ccui.Text wraps incorrectly and text is cut off:

```typescript
const text = new ccui.Text('This is a very long text that should wrap properly.', 'Arial', 16);
text.setPosition(200, 200);
this.addChild(text);
```

output:
The bug is that no text area size is set, so the text renders in a single line and may extend beyond the screen.

**Fix:** Set a text area size to enable word wrapping:

```typescript
const text = new ccui.Text('This is a very long text that should wrap properly.', 'Arial', 16);
text.setTextAreaSize(cc.size(250, 0)); // width=250, height=0 means auto height
text.setTextHorizontalAlignment(cc.TEXT_ALIGNMENT_LEFT);
text.setPosition(200, 200);
this.addChild(text);
```

Setting the width constrains line length, and height=0 allows the text to grow vertically as needed.

