```

The `trackIndex` parameter specifies which animation track (slot) to play on. Tracks are layered — track 0 is the base, and higher tracks overlay on top. This lets you blend independent animations simultaneously.

```typescript
const hero = new sp.SkeletonAnimation('res/hero/hero.json', 'res/hero/hero.atlas');
hero.setPosition(240, 160);
this.addChild(hero);

// Track 0: body movement (run, idle, jump)
hero.setAnimation(0, 'run', true);

// Track 1: facial overlay (blink, smile) — plays on top of track 0
hero.setAnimation(1, 'blink', true);

// Track 2: weapon overlay
hero.setAnimation(2, 'sword_swing', false);
```

Each track is independent — clearing or changing track 0 does not affect track 1. Higher-numbered tracks override bone transforms from lower tracks where they overlap. Use `clearTrack(trackIndex)` to stop a specific track or `clearTracks()` to stop all.

