instruction:
Find and fix the bug in this resource loading code:

```typescript
class Level {
    load(callback: () => void): void {
        cc.loader.loadJson('res/level.json', (err, data) => {
            this.levelData = data;
            callback();
        });
    }

    start(): void {
        this.load(() => {
            const enemies = this.levelData.enemies;
            enemies.forEach(e => this.spawnEnemy(e));
        });
    }
}
```

output:
Two bugs:

**Bug 1: No error handling.** If `loadJson` fails, `err` is non-null but the code ignores it. `data` will be `null`/`undefined`, and `this.levelData` becomes null. Then `this.levelData.enemies` throws a null reference error.

**Bug 2: `levelData` is untyped.** Accessing `.enemies` without type checking is fragile.

Fixed code:
```typescript
interface EnemyData {
    type: string;
    x: number;
    y: number;
}

interface LevelData {
    enemies: EnemyData[];
}

class Level {
    private levelData: LevelData | null = null;

    load(callback: (success: boolean) => void): void {
        cc.loader.loadJson('res/level.json', (err: any, data: any) => {
            if (err || !data) {
                cc.error('Failed to load level:', err);
                callback(false);
                return;
            }
            this.levelData = data as LevelData;
            callback(true);
        });
    }

    start(): void {
        this.load((success: boolean) => {
            if (!success || !this.levelData) {
                cc.error('Cannot start level — data not loaded');
                return;
            }
            const enemies = this.levelData.enemies;
            if (!enemies || !Array.isArray(enemies)) {
                cc.warn('No enemies in level data');
                return;
            }
            enemies.forEach(e => this.spawnEnemy(e));
        });
    }
}
```

Always check `err` in loader callbacks and validate data before use.

Reveal text character by character using scheduling:

```typescript
function typewriterEffect(
    parent: cc.Node, fullText: string, x: number, y: number,
    charDelay: number, onComplete?: () => void
): ccui.Text {
    const label = new ccui.Text('', 'Courier', 18);
    label.setTextAreaSize(cc.size(300, 0));
    label.setTextHorizontalAlignment(cc.TEXT_ALIGNMENT_LEFT);
    label.setAnchorPoint(cc.p(0, 1));
    label.setPosition(x, y);
    parent.addChild(label);

    let charIdx = 0;

    parent.schedule((dt: number) => {
        charIdx++;
        label.setString(fullText.substring(0, charIdx));
        if (charIdx >= fullText.length) {
            parent.unschedule(arguments.callee);
            if (onComplete) onComplete();
        }
    }, charDelay, fullText.length - 1, 0);

    return label;
}

// Usage:
