`cc.FLT_EPSILON` is a very small number used for safe floating-point comparisons:

```typescript
// Bad: direct equality check (unreliable with floats)
if (value === 0) { /* may fail */ }

// Good: epsilon comparison
if (Math.abs(value) < cc.FLT_EPSILON) {
    cc.log('Value is effectively zero');
}

// Common use: avoid dividing by zero vectors
const len = cc.pLength(direction);
if (len > cc.FLT_EPSILON) {
    const normalized = cc.pNormalize(direction);
    node.setPosition(cc.pAdd(pos, cc.pMult(normalized, speed * dt)));
}

// Compare two floating point values
function floatEquals(a: number, b: number): boolean {
    return Math.abs(a - b) < cc.FLT_EPSILON;
}
```

```typescript
cc.eventManager.dispatchCustomEvent(
    eventName: string | number,
    optionalUserData?: any
): void
```

Parameters:
- **`eventName`** — `string | number` identifying the custom event. Must match what listeners subscribed to.
- **`optionalUserData`** — optional `any` type. This data is attached to the event and retrievable via `event.getUserData<T>()` in listeners.

Return type: `void`

Examples:
```typescript
// Without data
cc.eventManager.dispatchCustomEvent('game:started');

// With primitive data
cc.eventManager.dispatchCustomEvent('timer:tick', 42);

// With object data (most common)
cc.eventManager.dispatchCustomEvent('enemy:spawned', {
    id: 'goblin_01',
    position: cc.p(200, 300),
    health: 50
});

// Receiving side:
cc.eventManager.addCustomListener('enemy:spawned', (event: cc.Event) => {
    const data = event.getUserData<{
        id: string;
        position: cc.Point;
        health: number;
    }>();
    cc.log(data.id, data.position.x, data.health);
});
```

Custom events defined in the Spine editor are delivered through the animation listener with type `sp.AnimationEventType.EVENT`. The `event` parameter contains the event data:

```typescript
const hero = new sp.SkeletonAnimation('res/hero/hero.json', 'res/hero/hero.atlas');
hero.setPosition(240, 160);
this.addChild(hero);
hero.setAnimation(0, 'run', true);

hero.setAnimationListener(this, (track: spine.TrackEntry, type: number, event: spine.Event) => {
    if (type === sp.AnimationEventType.EVENT) {
        const eventName = event.data.name;
        cc.log('Frame event: ' + eventName);

        if (eventName === 'footstep') {
            cc.audioEngine.playEffect('res/sfx_step.mp3');
        } else if (eventName === 'attack_hit') {
