`cc.Animation` holds a sequence of sprite frames. `cc.animate` creates an action that plays it:

**Creating an Animation:**
```typescript
// From sprite frames
const frames = [frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4];
const anim = new cc.Animation(frames, 0.1); // 0.1s per frame

// Or add frames one by one
const anim2 = new cc.Animation();
anim2.addSpriteFrame(frame1);
anim2.addSpriteFrame(frame2);
anim2.setDelayPerUnit(0.1);
```

**Configuration:**
```typescript
anim.setDelayPerUnit(0.08);          // seconds per frame
anim.setRestoreOriginalFrame(true);  // return to first frame after
anim.setLoops(3);                    // number of loops
```

**Playing:**
```typescript
// Play once
sprite.runAction(cc.animate(anim));

// Loop forever
sprite.runAction(cc.repeatForever(cc.animate(anim)));

// Play then remove
sprite.runAction(cc.sequence(
    cc.animate(anim),
    cc.removeSelf()
));
```

Total duration = `delayPerUnit * frameCount * loops`.

Use `getDeltaTime()`, `getSecondsPerFrame()`, and `getTotalFrames()` for profiling:

```typescript
class FrameProfiler extends cc.Layer {
    private _label: cc.LabelTTF;
    private _sampleCount: number = 0;
    private _dtAccum: number = 0;
    private _minDt: number = Infinity;
    private _maxDt: number = 0;
    private static readonly SAMPLE_SIZE = 60;

    onEnter(): void {
        super.onEnter();
        const winSize = cc.director.getWinSize();
        this._label = new cc.LabelTTF('', 'Courier', 12);
        this._label.setAnchorPoint(0, 1);
        this._label.setPosition(10, winSize.height - 10);
        this.addChild(this._label);
        this.scheduleUpdate();
    }

    update(dt: number): void {
        this._sampleCount++;
        this._dtAccum += dt;
        this._minDt = Math.min(this._minDt, dt);
        this._maxDt = Math.max(this._maxDt, dt);

        if (this._sampleCount >= FrameProfiler.SAMPLE_SIZE) {
            const avgFps = Math.round(this._sampleCount / this._dtAccum);
            const minFps = Math.round(1 / this._maxDt);
            const maxFps = Math.round(1 / this._minDt);
            const total = cc.director.getTotalFrames();
            this._label.setString(
                'FPS: ' + avgFps + ' (min:' + minFps + ' max:' + maxFps + ')\n' +
                'Total frames: ' + total
            );
            this._sampleCount = 0;
            this._dtAccum = 0;
            this._minDt = Infinity;
            this._maxDt = 0;
        }
    }
}
```

