panel.setSize(cc.size(300, 200));
panel.setClippingEnabled(true);
panel.setBackGroundColorType(ccui.Layout.BG_COLOR_SOLID);
panel.setBackGroundColor(cc.color(0, 0, 0));
panel.setBackGroundColorOpacity(180);
this.addChild(panel);
```

Always use `setBackGroundColorOpacity()` to control the alpha of layout backgrounds.

instruction:
Review this code for correctness:

```typescript
const draw = new cc.DrawNode();
this.addChild(draw);

// Draw concentric circles
for (let r = 10; r <= 100; r += 10) {
    draw.drawCircle(cc.p(240, 160), r, 0, r, false, 1, cc.color(255, 255, 255, 255));
}
```

output:
The code works but has a subtle issue: the `segments` parameter is set to `r` (the radius), which means inner circles use very few segments (10 for radius 10) while outer circles use many (100 for radius 100). Small circles with only 10 segments will look noticeably polygonal.

Fixed version:
```typescript
const draw = new cc.DrawNode();
this.addChild(draw);

const SEGMENTS = 32; // fixed segment count for smooth circles

for (let r = 10; r <= 100; r += 10) {
    draw.drawCircle(cc.p(240, 160), r, 0, SEGMENTS, false, 1, cc.color(255, 255, 255, 255));
}
```

Using a constant segment count (32 is a good default) ensures all circles render smoothly regardless of size.

Use `addAnimation` to queue animations after the current one on a given track. The `delay` parameter controls how many seconds to wait before the queued animation begins.

```typescript
const hero = new sp.SkeletonAnimation('res/hero/hero.json', 'res/hero/hero.atlas');
hero.setPosition(240, 160);
this.addChild(hero);

// Play jump once, then return to run loop
hero.setAnimation(0, 'jump', false);
hero.addAnimation(0, 'run', true, 0); // delay=0: start run immediately after jump ends

// More complex sequence: idle -> walk -> run
hero.setAnimation(0, 'idle', false);
hero.addAnimation(0, 'walk', false, 0);
hero.addAnimation(0, 'run', true, 0);
```

`addAnimation` returns a `spine.TrackEntry` for the queued entry. The `delay` is in seconds — use 0 to start right when the previous animation finishes, or a positive value to add a gap.

