Review this code:

```typescript
const children = node.getChildren();
for (let i = 0; i < children.length; i++) {
    node.removeChild(children[i]);
}
```

output:
**Issue:** Removing children while iterating over the children array causes index shifting. After removing child[0], child[1] becomes child[0], so the loop skips every other child.

**Fix:** Use `removeAllChildren` or iterate in reverse:

```typescript
// Option 1: Remove all (simplest)
node.removeAllChildren(true);

// Option 2: Reverse iteration
const children = node.getChildren().slice(); // copy the array
for (let i = children.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
    node.removeChild(children[i]);
}

// Option 3: Copy array first
const copy = [...node.getChildren()];
copy.forEach(child => node.removeChild(child));
```

