`popToSceneStackLevel` pops the scene stack down to a specific depth:

```typescript
cc.director.popToSceneStackLevel(level: number): void
```

Stack levels are 0-based:
- Level 0: empty (results in `end()`)
- Level 1: root scene only
- Level N: keep N scenes on stack

```typescript
// Example navigation flow:
// Stack: [MenuScene]  (level 1)
cc.director.runScene(new MenuScene());

// Stack: [MenuScene, GameScene]  (level 2)
cc.director.pushScene(new GameScene());

// Stack: [MenuScene, GameScene, PauseScene]  (level 3)
cc.director.pushScene(new PauseScene());

// Stack: [MenuScene, GameScene, PauseScene, SettingsScene]  (level 4)
cc.director.pushScene(new SettingsScene());

// Pop back to GameScene (level 2)
cc.director.popToSceneStackLevel(2);
// Stack: [MenuScene, GameScene]

// Pop to root (level 1)
cc.director.popToRootScene(); // equivalent to popToSceneStackLevel(1)
// Stack: [MenuScene]
```

