You can control speed at two levels — globally on the skeleton, or per-track on the `TrackEntry`:

```typescript
const hero = new sp.SkeletonAnimation('res/hero/hero.json', 'res/hero/hero.atlas');
hero.setPosition(240, 160);
this.addChild(hero);

// Global time scale — affects ALL tracks
hero.setTimeScale(0.5);  // half speed (slow motion)
hero.setTimeScale(1.0);  // normal speed
hero.setTimeScale(2.0);  // double speed

const currentScale = hero.getTimeScale();

// Per-track speed via TrackEntry
const track = hero.setAnimation(0, 'attack', false);
if (track) {
    track.timeScale = 2.0;  // only this track plays at 2x
}
```

`setTimeScale` on the skeleton multiplies with the per-track `timeScale`. So if skeleton timeScale is 0.5 and track timeScale is 2.0, the effective speed is 1.0.

