instruction:
Find and fix the bug in this color creation code:

```typescript
const red = cc.color(255, 0, 0);
const fadeRed = cc.color(red.r, red.g, red.b, 0.5);
sprite.setColor(fadeRed);
```

output:
The bug is that `0.5` is passed for the alpha component, but `cc.Color` expects integer values 0-255, not floating point 0-1.

Fixed code:
```typescript
const red = cc.color(255, 0, 0);
const fadeRed = cc.color(red.r, red.g, red.b, 128);  // 128 = ~50% alpha
sprite.setColor(fadeRed);
```

Also note that `setColor` on a `cc.Sprite` only affects RGB tinting — it does not set alpha. To set transparency, use `setOpacity`:

```typescript
const red = cc.color(255, 0, 0);
sprite.setColor(red);
sprite.setOpacity(128); // 50% transparency
```

Jump actions create parabolic movement:

```typescript
// jumpTo(duration, position, height, numJumps)
node.runAction(cc.jumpTo(1.0, cc.p(300, 100), 80, 3));
// Jumps to (300,100) with 3 bounces reaching 80px high

// jumpBy(duration, delta, height, numJumps)
node.runAction(cc.jumpBy(1.0, cc.p(200, 0), 60, 2));
// Jumps rightward 200px with 2 bounces

// Also with separate x,y:
node.runAction(cc.jumpTo(1.0, 300, 100, 80, 3));
```

