For custom HTTP requests, use `cc.loader.getXMLHttpRequest()`:
```typescript
function loadRemoteJson(url: string, cb: (err: any, data: any) => void): void {
    const xhr = cc.loader.getXMLHttpRequest();
    xhr.open('GET', url, true);
    xhr.onreadystatechange = function() {
        if (xhr.readyState === 4) {
            if (xhr.status === 200) {
                cb(null, JSON.parse(xhr.responseText));
            } else {
                cb(new Error('HTTP ' + xhr.status), null);
            }
        }
    };
    xhr.send();
}
```

The `isCrossOrigin` option sets CORS headers. Only relevant in H5; native platforms have no cross-origin restrictions.

