`cc.repeat` runs an action a fixed number of times. `cc.repeatForever` loops indefinitely.

**`cc.repeat(action, times)`:**
```typescript
// Bounce 3 times
const bounce = cc.sequence(
    cc.moveBy(0.3, cc.p(0, 50)),
    cc.moveBy(0.3, cc.p(0, -50))
);
node.runAction(cc.repeat(bounce, 3));
// Total duration: 3 * 0.6 = 1.8 seconds, then stops
```

**`cc.repeatForever(action)`:**
```typescript
// Bounce forever
node.runAction(cc.repeatForever(bounce));
// Never stops — must be stopped manually
```

Key differences:
- `repeat` can be inside a `cc.sequence` (it has finite duration)
- `repeatForever` CANNOT be inside a sequence (infinite duration blocks subsequent actions)
- `repeatForever` must be stopped with `stopAction` or `stopAllActions`
- Both available as chain methods: `action.repeat(3)` and `action.repeatForever()`

Layers and their children are cleaned up automatically when a scene is replaced, but here are best practices:

```typescript
class GameLayer extends cc.Layer {
    private scheduledCallbacks: Function[] = [];

    init(): boolean {
        this.scheduleUpdate();
        return true;
    }

    onExit(): void {
        // Unschedule everything
        this.unscheduleAllCallbacks();

        // Remove all children
        this.removeAllChildren(true);  // true = cleanup

        super.onExit();
    }

    update(dt: number): void {
        // Game logic
    }
}

// Scene transition cleans up old scene
const newScene = new cc.Scene();
newScene.addChild(new MenuLayer());

// replaceScene removes and cleans up the old scene
cc.director.runScene(newScene);

// For LayerMultiplex, release unused layers
const multiplex = new cc.LayerMultiplex(layer1, layer2);
// When done with layer1 permanently:
multiplex.switchToAndReleaseMe(1);  // releases layer1
```

Key points:
- `cc.director.runScene` replaces the current scene and triggers cleanup on the old one
- Override `onExit()` for custom cleanup (unschedule, remove listeners)
- `removeAllChildren(true)` cleans up children recursively
- Use `switchToAndReleaseMe` in `cc.LayerMultiplex` for one-time layers
- Children added with `addChild` are automatically cleaned up when the parent is removed

