`willPlayMusic()` and `isMusicPlaying()` check different conditions:

**`isMusicPlaying(): boolean`**
- Returns `true` if music is actively playing right now
- Returns `false` if music is paused, stopped, or never started

**`willPlayMusic(): boolean`**
- Returns `true` if the music system is ready and able to play
- Checks if music is loaded and the audio engine is initialized

```typescript
// Music not started yet
cc.log(cc.audioEngine.isMusicPlaying());  // false
cc.log(cc.audioEngine.willPlayMusic());   // true (engine is ready)

// Start music
cc.audioEngine.playMusic('res/audio/bgm.mp3', true);
cc.log(cc.audioEngine.isMusicPlaying());  // true

// Pause
cc.audioEngine.pauseMusic();
cc.log(cc.audioEngine.isMusicPlaying());  // false (paused)
cc.log(cc.audioEngine.willPlayMusic());   // true (can resume)

// After end()
cc.audioEngine.end();
cc.log(cc.audioEngine.willPlayMusic());   // false (engine shut down)
```

Use `isMusicPlaying()` to check current playback state. Use `willPlayMusic()` to check if the audio system is operational before attempting to play.

