`cc.formatStr` creates formatted strings similar to `printf`:

```typescript
cc.formatStr(...args: any[]): string
```

Examples:
```typescript
// Basic formatting
const msg1 = cc.formatStr('Player %s has %d coins', 'Alice', 150);
// 'Player Alice has 150 coins'

// Use with cc.log
cc.log(cc.formatStr('Level %d completed in %d seconds', 3, 42));

// Multiple arguments
const msg2 = cc.formatStr('Position: (%d, %d), Health: %d/%d', 100, 200, 75, 100);
// 'Position: (100, 200), Health: 75/100'

