Find and fix the bug in this code that tries to chain animations:

```typescript
ccs.armatureDataManager.addArmatureFileInfo('res/hero/hero.ExportJson');
const armature = ccs.Armature.create('hero');
this.addChild(armature);

armature.animation.play('attack', -1, 0);
armature.animation.play('idle', 5, -1);
```

output:
The bug is that both `play` calls execute immediately. The second `play('idle')` immediately overrides the first `play('attack')`, so the attack animation never actually plays.

To chain animations, use `setMovementEventCallFunc` to wait for the first animation to complete:

Fixed code:
```typescript
ccs.armatureDataManager.addArmatureFileInfo('res/hero/hero.ExportJson');
const armature = ccs.Armature.create('hero');
this.addChild(armature);

// Listen for completion, then transition to idle
armature.animation.setMovementEventCallFunc((arm, type, id) => {
    if (type === ccs.MovementEventType.COMPLETE && id === 'attack') {
        arm.animation.play('idle', 5, -1);
    }
});

armature.animation.play('attack', -1, 0);
```

Alternatively, use `playWithNames` to sequence them:
```typescript
armature.animation.playWithNames(['attack', 'idle'], 5, false);
```

