Fix the bug. The layout children overlap instead of stacking vertically:

```typescript
const layout = new ccui.Layout();
layout.setSize(cc.size(300, 500));
layout.setLayoutType(ccui.Layout.ABSOLUTE);
for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
    const btn = new ccui.Button('btn.png');
    layout.addChild(btn);
}
this.addChild(layout);
```

output:
The bug is that the layout type is `ABSOLUTE`, which means children are freely positioned and don't auto-stack. Change it to `LINEAR_VERTICAL`:

```typescript
const layout = new ccui.Layout();
layout.setSize(cc.size(300, 500));
layout.setLayoutType(ccui.Layout.LINEAR_VERTICAL);
for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
    const btn = new ccui.Button('btn.png');
    const param = new ccui.LinearLayoutParameter();
    param.setGravity(ccui.LinearLayoutParameter.CENTER_HORIZONTAL);
    param.setMargin(new ccui.Margin(0, 5, 0, 0));
    btn.setLayoutParameter(param);
    layout.addChild(btn);
}
layout.forceDoLayout();
this.addChild(layout);
```

```typescript
function isFullyInside(inner: cc.Node, outer: cc.Node): boolean {
    const innerBox: cc.Rect = inner.getBoundingBox();
    const outerBox: cc.Rect = outer.getBoundingBox();
    return cc.rectContainsRect(outerBox, innerBox);
}

// Usage: check if player is within safe zone
const player = new cc.Sprite('res/player.png');
const safeZone = new cc.Node();
safeZone.setContentSize(cc.size(300, 200));
safeZone.setPosition(240, 160);

if (isFullyInside(player, safeZone)) {
    cc.log('Player is completely within safe zone');
}
```

Signature: `cc.rectContainsRect(rect1: cc.Rect, rect2: cc.Rect): boolean`

Returns `true` only if `rect1` completely contains `rect2` — all four corners of `rect2` must be inside `rect1`. This is stricter than `cc.rectOverlapsRect` which only requires partial overlap.

